### Run DEV first — rows land with source='DEV'
POST http://localhost:4105/pipeline/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Shipments_DEV","mode":"delta","trigger":"manual"}

### Then PROD — rows land with source='PROD', DEV rows untouched
POST http://localhost:4105/pipeline/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Shipments_PROD","mode":"delta","trigger":"manual"}

### Consolidated view — rows from both origins coexist via the `source` key
GET http://localhost:4105/odata/v4/example/Shipments?$orderby=source,modifiedAt desc

### Filter by origin
GET http://localhost:4105/odata/v4/example/Shipments?$filter=source eq 'DEV'
GET http://localhost:4105/odata/v4/example/Shipments?$filter=source eq 'PROD'

### Per-origin flush — drop DEV, leave PROD intact.
POST http://localhost:4105/pipeline/flush
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Shipments_DEV"}

### Confirm — only PROD rows survive.
GET http://localhost:4105/odata/v4/example/Shipments?$orderby=source

### Re-run DEV — brings it back.
POST http://localhost:4105/pipeline/execute
Content-Type: application/json

{"name":"Shipments_DEV","mode":"delta","trigger":"manual"}
